title: Grateful Dead Live at Manhattan Center on 1971-04-06
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Beat It On Down The Line, It Hurts Me Too, Me And Bobby McGee, Dire Wolf, Oh Boy, Hog For You Baby, Playin' In The Band, Midnight Hour, Mama Tried, Cumberland Blues, Casey Jones

Set 2

Greatest Story Ever Told-> Johnny B. Goode, Loser, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin', Sugar Magnolia, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away-> Truckin'

'Dance Marathon' - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: - Easily the best SBD version so far. Though the first set is very lazy indeed, the second (especially the last half or so) is superlative.
represents This is a stellar April '71 show. Bertha, Greatest and Sugar Mag are tasty and the (stand alone) NFA reprise and Truckin' are the death!
Very Nice, Spin It Highlights: Oh Boy, Hog For You Baby, Greatest Story Ever Told, Good Lovin'
